com.vmware.vcenter.namespace_management.supervisors

Interface Summary

  • All Superinterfaces:
    com.vmware.vapi.internal.bindings.CompletionStageService, com.vmware.vapi.bindings.Service, SummaryTypes
    All Known Implementing Classes:
    SummaryStub

    public interface Summary
extends com.vmware.vapi.bindings.Service, SummaryTypes, com.vmware.vapi.internal.bindings.CompletionStageService

    The Summary interface provides methods to retrieve the current states of Supervisors.

    Only the basic information of the given Supervisor is being queried.

    . This interface was added in vSphere API 8.0.0.1.

    • Method Detail

      • get

        Summary.GetInvocation get(java.lang.String supervisor)
        Queries the current state of the specified Supervisor. This method was added in vSphere API 8.0.0.1.

        Invocation Result:
        SummaryTypes.Info of the Supervisor matching the provided identifier.

        Parameters:
        supervisor - the identifier for a supervisor The parameter must be an identifier for the resource type: com.vmware.vcenter.namespace_management.supervisor.Supervisor.
        Returns:
        instance of Summary.GetInvocation which upon invoke executes the above described get operation. The operation result or the operation error will be stored in the CompletionStageFuture that invoke returns.
        Throws:
        Error - if the system reports an error while responding to the request.
        Error - if the system reports an error while responding to the request.
        NotFound - if the Supervisor matching the ID does not exist.
        Unauthenticated - if the user can not be authenticated.
        Unauthenticated - if the user can not be authenticated.
        Unauthorized - if the user does not have Namespaces.Manage privilege and the System.Read privilege on all vSphere Clusters hosting the Supervisor.

      • list

        Summary.ListInvocation list()
        Queries the current state of all Supervisors. Optionally, apply the filter to Supervisors that match the criteria in the SummaryTypes.FilterSpec. This method was added in vSphere API 8.0.0.1.

        Invocation Result:
        ListResult of SummaryTypes.Info of all Supervisors matching the criteria in the SummaryTypes.FilterSpec.

        Returns:
        instance of Summary.ListInvocation which upon invoke executes the above described list operation. The operation result or the operation error will be stored in the CompletionStageFuture that invoke returns.
        Throws:
        Error - if the system reports an error while responding to the request.
        Unauthenticated - if the user can not be authenticated.
        Unauthorized - if the user does not have Namespaces.Manage privilege and the System.Read privilege on all vSphere Clusters hosting the Supervisor.
